<h1>Supplementary References on ICS 4 Course Topics</h1>
<p>These links and books explain or illustrate some of the topics we've covered in lecture, typically in more detail than we've seen in class. They're supplementary, not assigned, unless we say otherwise.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Jakob Nielsen's <a href="http://www.useit.com/alertbox/9605.html">Top Ten Mistakes in Web Design</a></li>
  <li>Web design/development books for those with a more technical background
  <ul>
    <li><em><a href="http://headfirstlabs.books/hfwd/">Head First Web Design</a></em> by Watrall and Siarto </li>
  <li><a href="http://www.webstepbook.com/"><em>Web Programming Step by Step</em></a> by Stepp, Miller, and Kirst</li>
  </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
